ce:section.ce:para:
The electrochemical properties of the as-fabricated catalysts for OER were investigated in 1.0 M KOH. For comparison, the LSV curves of CoSe2/NF, CoSe2/NCDs/NF-1, CoSe2/NCDs/NF-2, CoSe2/NCDs/NF-3, CoSe2/NCDs/NF-4 and CoSe2/NCDs/NF-6 were also analyzed under the same condition. As displayed in Fig. 5
                        a, CoSe2/NF shows negligible OER activities, whereas after adding the NCDs, the catalytic activity of CoSe2/NCDs/NF is obviously improved. Notably, CoSe2/NCDs/NF-5 manifests the higher catalytic activity with a low overpotential of only 268 mV at 70 mA cm−2, which is much lower than those of the counterparts owing to the strong synergistic effect between CoSe2 and NCDs components. More remarkable, the catalytic performance of CoSe2/NCDs/NF-5 is superior to the most reported Co-based catalysts composed of non-noble metal (Table S1
                        ), including (such as) Co-based hybrid phosphates (296 mV) [42], Mn-CoSe2/CFC (300 mV) [13], emphasizing its excellent activity for OER electrocatalysis.
